NAME: tail
DESCRIPTION:
Print the lasts [-n number] lines of a file named [file].
	Print the lasts 10 lines if [-n number] option is not given.

	Example to print the lasts 10 lines of a file named README.md.
		tail README.md
	Example to print the lasts 2 lines of a file named README.md.
		tail -n 2 README.md

	See also head.
